7 An Act relating to alcoholic beverages; requiring the
Alcoholic Beverage Laws Enforcement (ABLE) Commission
8 to issue multiple licenses for manufacturing
beverages on the same premises to certain license
9 holders; providing requirements for acquiring
multiple licenses; requiring a license holder
10 operating under an alternating proprietorship or
premises arrangement to abide by the Oklahoma
11 Alcoholic Beverage Control Act; directing the ABLE
Commission to promulgate rules to authorize
12 alternating proprietorship or premises; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-165 of Title 37A, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. The Alcoholic Beverage Laws Enforcement (ABLE) Commission
20 shall issue multiple licenses for manufacturing beverages on the
21 same premises if the applicant is in good standing with the ABLE
22 Commission and the Oklahoma Tax Commission pursuant to the Oklahoma
23 Alcoholic Beverage Control Act including, but not limited to, small
24 brewer license, charitable collaboration brewer license, distiller
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3501 Page 1

1 lice nse, winemaker license, rectifier license, and small farm winery
2 license and manufacturer's license. Nothing in this section shall
3 be construed to apply to the issuance of distribution or wholesale
4 licensee.
5 B. Applicants for an additional license must obtain all
6 necessary federal permits and approvals from the Alcohol and Tobacco
7 Tax and Trade Bureau (TTB) for an alternating proprietorship or
8 premises arrangement and the applicant must be in good standing with
9 the TTB. An applicant shall notify the ABLE Commission of its
10 intention to operate an alternating proprietorship or premises when
11 applying for the second and all subsequent licenses for a single
12 premises.
13 C. Any license holder operating under an alternating
14 proprietorship or premises arrangement shall abide by the portions
15 of the Oklahoma Alcoholic Beverage Control Act that are relevant to
16 the license under which they are producing the corresponding
17 beverage governed by the license.
18 D. The ABLE Commission shall promulgate rules, pursuant to the
19 Administrative Procedures Act, to authorize alternating
20 proprietorship or premises arrangements.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
